data.name: TextBox_Keywords.ToolTip
data.value: Obviate bad sentence structures by defining keywords for your emotes. PetEmote will compare the keywords of all emotes to each other, to see which emotes go together with others well and which do not. Using the same keyword for different emotes, no matter on which level they are, will prevent PetEmote from using these emotes in the same sentence.

data.name: ToolStripComboBox_Chance.ToolTipText
data.value:
Choose a number from 1 to 200, which represents a percental chance, that the selected emote occurs in comparison with other emotes of the same level.
- with a value of 100, the emote occurs as often as any other emote - a value greater than 100 increases the chance, that the emote occurs - a value lower than 100 decreases the chance, that the emote occurs - a value of 200 doubles the chance, that the emote occurs - with a value of 1 the emote occurs extremely rare
